snippet: Cardinal Timothy M. Dolan, who celebrated Mass at St. Patrick’s Cathedral on Ash Wednesday, told worshipers that Benedict XVI was “aware of his own limitations, as we all have to be.”
abstract: Cardinal Timothy M Dolan, archbishop of New York, says resignation of Pope Benedict XVI is living example of humility and penance, message of Ash Wednesday.
lead_paragraph: Cardinal Timothy M. Dolan, who celebrated Mass at St. Patrick’s Cathedral on Ash Wednesday, told worshipers that Benedict XVI was “aware of his own limitations, as we all have to be.”

headline.seo: Cardinal Dolan Calls Pope’s Resignation a Sign of Humility
headline.main: Cardinal Dolan Calls Pope’s Resignation a Sign of Humility
headline.print_headline: Dolan Says Pope’s Action Is a Sign Of Humility
